    "For any d ≥ 1, the smallest possible value ofτ φ,d is τ φ,d = σ -1 d, achieved when H φ,d = V d.Definition 2 (Spectral features).",
    "We say that the features φ and ψ are spectral features ifH φ,d = span{v 1,..., v d } = V d and H ψ,d = span{u 1,..., u d } = U d.By Proposition 2, spectral features minimize the sieve measure of ill-posedness, and therefore the estimation error term.",
    "This leads to the following corollary.Corollary 1 (Sieve 2SLS with spectral features).",
